This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as it deals with subspace recovery from data. It may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category, as it discusses the theoretical foundations of the models. Additionally, it involves optimization and computational complexity, which could place it in the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the use of randomized algorithms suggests that it could also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
